title: 820-2850 1/4 fan spin
message: You answered the question already, or do you think missing 1v05_s5 is normal?

title: 820-2850 1/4 fan spin
message:
well the only thing i am confused about is where 1v05_s5 is getting connected to power if U7740 is not attached, also c7740 and c7741, r1825 etc  are also not attached those are the only places on the board 1v05_s5 shows up.  and they are not suppose to be there i checked with other boards, but the schematics do not say no stuff.   

should PP18V5_S3  be present also?

title: 820-2850 1/4 fan spin
message:
Ugh, so you didn't even check if the parts are even on the board. Of course there is no 1V05_s5 if U7740 is not there. Look at the note with U7740 why they thought it might be needed.
18V5 is for trackpad, who cares?

Where was liquid damage?

title: 820-2850 1/4 fan spin
message: okay i understand.  right that is what i was thinking.  the liquid shows bad signs around the graphics and cpu,  also like wise on the back side center top area everywhere around the isl6263, i ran it through the UC because it was under the big chips.

title: 820-2850 1/4 fan spin
message: Could be corrosion under CPU/GPU. Check all traces and resistors around ISL6263.
